27/04/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Economy Minister Lidia Shuleva said Monday (26 April) that the cabinet is formulating new government priorities.
While several alternatives are under consideration, four major areas are involved:
improving the national road infrastructure, enhancing competitiveness and encouraging investments, implementing educational reforms and resolving local government problems.
In other news, the government commission on building a new nuclear plant announced Monday that an investor would be selected through direct talks rather than a tender.
Bulgaria is to build a new facility in Belene to compensate for the closure of several units at the Kozloduy nuclear power plant.
(24 Chasa - 27/04/04;
BTA, Standart - 26/04/04)
